{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:52:16.801Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Training a neural network requires a scalar score that says how wrong the predictions are. Loss functions define that score; minimizing loss via gradient descent is how LLMs learn to predict the next token, classify intent, and align with human preferences."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "loss function",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (or cost function) maps model predictions and ground-truth targets to a single non-negative number. Lower is better. Training adjusts weights to minimize expected loss over a dataset. Regression often uses "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "mean squared error (MSE)",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "; classification and language modeling use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cross-entropy",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " variants."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM pretraining optimizes cross-entropy over next-token prediction across billions of tokens. Fine-tuning, RLHF, and distillation all redefine or augment the loss. The loss landscape—how loss changes as weights move—determines whether training converges, diverges, or gets stuck. Reading training logs (loss curves, perplexity) requires knowing what is being measured."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mean squared error (MSE)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "MSE = (1/n) Σ (y_pred - y_true)²",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Penalizes large errors quadratically. Used for regression (predicting numbers). Differentiable; gradient is proportional to error."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\n\npred = torch.tensor([2.5, 0.0, 2.1])\ntarget = torch.tensor([3.0, -0.5, 2.0])\nloss = nn.MSELoss()(pred, target)\nprint(loss.item())  # scalar"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cross-entropy for classification"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For true class "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "y",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and predicted probability "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "p",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "CE = -log(p_y)",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Encourages the model to assign high probability to the correct class. With logits "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "z",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "nn.CrossEntropyLoss",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " combines softmax and negative log-likelihood in one stable operation."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "logits = torch.tensor([[2.0, 1.0, 0.1]])  # one sample, 3 classes\ntarget = torch.tensor([0])                   # true class index\n\ncriterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\nloss = criterion(logits, target)\nprint(loss.item())"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Language modeling loss"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each token position produces logits over the vocabulary; the target is the next token ID. Loss is averaged over all non-masked positions in the batch. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Perplexity",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "exp(average_cross_entropy)",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "—lower perplexity means the model is less \"surprised\" by held-out text."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# logits: (batch, seq_len, vocab_size)\n# labels: (batch, seq_len) — next token ids; -100 ignores padding\nloss = F.cross_entropy(\n    logits.view(-1, vocab_size),\n    labels.view(-1),\n    ignore_index=-100,\n)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Other losses in the LLM ecosystem"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Binary cross-entropy",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — multi-label or yes/no heads (e.g., safety classifiers)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "KL divergence",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — distillation: student model matches teacher distribution"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Reward modeling loss",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — preference pairs in RLHF pipelines"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Regularization terms",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — weight decay (L2) added to loss to prevent overfitting"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Examples"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Minimal training step showing loss driving weight updates:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "model = nn.Linear(10, 3)\noptimizer = torch.optim.SGD(model.parameters(), lr=0.01)\ncriterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n\nx = torch.randn(8, 10)\nlabels = torch.randint(0, 3, (8,))\n\noptimizer.zero_grad()\nlogits = model(x)\nloss = criterion(logits, labels)\nloss.backward()\noptimizer.step()\nprint(f\"loss={loss.item():.4f}\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "MSE sensitivity",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — outliers dominate due to squaring; Huber loss is more robust for some regression tasks."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cross-entropy and overconfidence",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — models can become overconfident on training data; label smoothing mitigates this."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Class imbalance",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — rare classes contribute little to average loss; weighted cross-entropy or focal loss rebalances."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Next-token loss vs downstream quality",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — lower pretraining loss correlates with capability but does not guarantee instruction-following or safety."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Applying softmax before CrossEntropyLoss",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — double application hurts numerics; pass logits directly."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Wrong target dtype",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — CrossEntropyLoss expects class indices (LongTensor), not one-hot floats."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Not masking padding tokens",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — padding positions inflate or distort the loss average in sequence models."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Monitoring loss alone",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — loss can decrease while validation quality plateaus (overfitting); track held-out metrics."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "ignore_index",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " for padding in sequence cross-entropy."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Log both loss and perplexity during LM training for interpretability."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Apply label smoothing (e.g., 0.1) when fine-tuning classifiers on small datasets."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Separate training loss from evaluation metrics (accuracy, BLEU, human preference)—optimize one, report others."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mental model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Loss is a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "distance meter",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " between what the model predicted and what should have happened. Cross-entropy asks: \"How many bits of surprise did we assign to the correct answer?\" Training nudges every weight slightly to reduce that surprise on average. An LLM that assigns 90% probability to the wrong next word gets a steep penalty; assigning 90% to the right word gets a small loss."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Loss converts predictions + targets into one differentiable number to minimize."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "MSE for regression; cross-entropy for classification and next-token prediction in LLMs."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Perplexity = exp(cross-entropy)—standard LM quality indicator."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Pass logits to CrossEntropyLoss; mask padding with ignore_index."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Training loss trends matter, but downstream evaluation confirms real capability."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
